A prominent politician in Kebbi State,Alhaji Dan Musa Ribah and his followers have defected to Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Kebbi. The Chairman of Peoples Democratic Party in Kebbi ,Alhaji Haruna Saidu revealed this in Ribah, Danko Wasagu local government area of Kebbi State at the weekend. He said Alhaji Dan Musa could not attend the ceremony organized for him and his followers in Ribah because he was taken away by unknown persons. Saidu explained that prior to the defection ceremony, the politician informed him that he decided to left APC because the party has not been beneficial to him and chieftain of the party deserted him. “” He gave me his words that he left APC for PDP because he has not benefitted with his people from APC””,he said The PDP governorship candidate, Senator Isah Galaudu assured the defectors of equal treatment in the party . He expressed delight that the PDP is waxing stronger in Kebbi and promised to offer credible leadership . “” If elected in 2019 ,I will offer good Leadership and transparent government for the good of all “”, he said. 